obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32602)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Provisions in respect of the State Bank Dholpur.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00030_196256_1517807322465&sectionId=32602&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00030_196256_1517807322465
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any other law or in any order or other instrument--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government may by order appoint one or more officers to take over the`
  line `management of the Dholpur bank or to wind up its affairs and distribute its assets and any expenditure`
  line `incurred in connection with such appointment, management, winding up or distribution shall be`
  line `payable by that bank;`
  line
  line `(b) the principal civil court of original jurisdiction in the district in which the Dholpur bank's`
  line `head office is situated shall have exclusive jurisdiction to entertain and decide any claim made by or`
  line `against the Dholpur bank or any question whatever, whether of law or of fact, which may relate to or`
  line `arise in the course of the winding up of that bank, whether such claim or question has accrued or`
  line `arisen before or accrues or arises after the date of the winding up order, and any suit or other legal`
  line `proceeding, whether of a civil or criminal nature, relating to any such claim or question and pending`
  line `in any other court at the commencement of this Act shall not be proceeded with except in accordance`
  line `with this section;`
  line
  line `(c) in regard to the admissibility of the entries in the books of account as evidence in the course of`
  line `the proceedings for the winding up of the bank, the settlement of the list of debtors of the bank, the`
  line `passing of orders for the payment of the amounts due by the said debtors, the execution of the said`
  line `orders or any other orders or decrees of the court, the priority of the claims on the bank, the making of`
  line `preferential payments and the discharge of the other liabilities of the bank and any other incidental or`
  line `connected matters, the law relating to the winding up of banking companies, as in force for the time`
  line `being, shall apply as if the Dholpur bank were a banking company;`
  line
  line `(d) the period of limitation for any suit or application relating to any payment due to the Dholpur`
  line `bank which has accrued before or may accrue on or after the date of the first appointment of the`
  line `officer in change of winding up of the bank shall be twelve years from the date of the accrual of the`
  line `claim or five years from the date of such first appointment of the officer aforesaid, whichever may`
  line `end later; and`
  line
  line `(e) after the repayment of all the deposit liabilities and any other amounts due to be paid by the`
  line `bank including the amounts due to the Government of Rajasthan, the remaining assets, if any, of the`
  line `bank shall be utilised, as far as may be, for the purposes and objects specified in the State Bank,`
  line `Dholpur Act, 1915, and other relevant documents.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section, "Dholpur bank" means the bank known as the Dholpur State Bank and governed at`
  line `the commencement of this section by the State Bank, Dholpur Act, 1915.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
